      • movePlayer

        public Player movePlayer(Player movingP,
                         int amount)
        Moves the selected player square by square until the number of moves its equal to 0, if the next square its null and it still has movements then the method returns the player that won
        Parameters:
        movingP - it's the player that its going to move
        amount - the number of movements in the board
        Returns:
        The player that won if its the case, otherwise returns null

      • isPlayerOn

        public int isPlayerOn(Player current,
                      java.lang.String symbol,
                      int index)
        Check if the given player its located in this square
        Parameters:
        current - The linked list of players located in this square
        symbol - The symbol of player that its goin to search
        index - Its the counter to return the index where the player is located
        Returns:
        The index where the player was found if its the case, otherwise returns -1

      • getSquaresInARow

        public Square getSquaresInARow(Square a,
                               int selectedRow)
        Get all the Squares in the linked list that are located in the same row (given by Board)
        Parameters:
        a - Its the linked list of Squares where the method will add the requested Squares
        selectedRow - Its the number of the row that it has to search
        Returns:
